# Tailwind CSS Rules

## Setup
- Tailwind content globs should include `./pages/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}` and `./components/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}`.
- Import Tailwind layers in `styles/globals.css` in this order: `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities;`.

## Theme
- Colors
  - Primary: `#4F46E5` (indigo)
  - Background: `#FFFFFF` or `#F9FAFB`
  - Text (body): `#1F2937` with subtler text `#4B5563`
- Typography
  - Use Inter or Manrope via `next/font`.
  - Set the font on `<body>` and rely on Tailwind `font-sans`.

Extend `tailwind.config.js` minimally, e.g.:
```
theme: {
  extend: {
    colors: {
      primary: '#4F46E5',
    },
  },
}
```

## Conventions
- Prefer utility classes; avoid custom CSS unless global typography or resets.
- Use the `container` utility with appropriate responsive paddings for section widths.
- Build repeatable patterns (e.g., section spacing, grid gaps) with small composition classes, not custom CSS.
- Keep class lists readable: group by box model, layout, typography, color, state.

## Components
- Hero, Features, Demo, CTA should be responsive by default (sm/md/lg breakpoints).
- Use semantic spacing scale (e.g., `py-16 md:py-24`).
- Use accessible color contrast; validate primary on light background.

## Performance
- Avoid arbitrary values unless justified; prefer theme tokens.
- Remove unused classes by keeping content globs accurate.

